 attachment to his new landscape." Prairie Forum    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFrontier and pioneer lifezManitoba. 0aImmigrantszManitobavCorrespondence. 0aPioneerszManitobavCorrespondence. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh  asettler, narrative, Manitoba history.1 aCoates, Ken S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMorrison, Bill, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311127402708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015z978311127703540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088977409440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889774094423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889774094/original  a978-3-11-127402-7  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-127703-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles